The '''International Code of Area Nomenclature''' ('''ICAN''') provides a universal naming system or [[nomenclature]] for areas of [[endemism]] used in [[biogeography]] and elsewhere. The ICAN also serves as the [[international standard]] rules for proposing and using area names.<ref>{{citejournal|author=Ebach, M.C., Morrone, J.J. Parenti, L.R. & Viloria Á.L.|year=2008|title=International Code of Area Nomenclature|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1365-2699.2008.01920.x/abstract|journal=Journal of Biogeography|volume=35|issue=7|pages= 1153–1157}}</ref>

The ICAN was ratified by the [[Systematic and evolutionary biogeography association|Systematic and Evolutionary Biogeographical Association (SEBA)]]<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://biogeographyportal.free.fr/|title=Systematic and Evolutionary Biogeographical Association}}</ref> in [[Paris]] during July 2007.

