{{Infobox scientist | name = Margaret Buckingham | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = <!-- (!--(as myimage.jpg, no 'File:')--> | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1945|03|02}} | birth_place = Scotland | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | other_names = | residence = France | citizenship = dual French-British | nationality = British | fields = | workplaces = | alma_mater = [[University of Oxford]] | thesis_title = | thesis_url = | thesis_year = 1971 | doctoral_advisor = | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | influences = | influenced = | honorific_suffix = [[Foreign Member of the Royal Society|ForMemRS]] | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = {{url|http://www.optistem.org/about-us/principal-investigators/margaret-buckingham}} | footnotes = | spouse = | children = }} '''Margaret Buckingham''', {{post-nominals|country=UK|HonFRSE|post-noms=[[Foreign Member of the Royal Society|ForMemRS]]}}, is a [[developmental biologist]] working in the fields of [[myogenesis]] and [[cardiogenesis]]. She is a professor emeritus at the [[Pasteur Institute]] in Paris and exceptional grade senior researcher emeritus at the [[Centre national de la recherche scientifique]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.consulfrance-vancouver.org/Developmental-biologist-Margaret |title=Developmental biologist Margaret Buckingham is awarded the 2013 CNRS Gold Medal |date= |work= |publisher= Consulate General of France in Vancouver |doi= |isbn= |accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref> She is a member of the [[European Molecular Biology Organization]], the [[Academia Europaea]] and the [[French Academy of Sciences]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://royalsociety.org/people/margaret-buckingham/ |title=Professor Margaret Buckingham ForMemRS |date= |work= |publisher=The Royal Society |doi= |isbn= |accessdate=5 May 2013}}</ref>
== Education and early career == After graduating from [[Oxford University]], where her thesis was on [[histone]] modifications, she joined F. Gros's laboratory at the [[Pasteur Institute]] to work on mRNA regulation during skeletal muscle differentiation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ged.aeres-evaluation.fr/guest.php?sole=Y&app=AERES_DIFFCV&action=AERES_DIFFCV_DOWNLOAD_CV&id=74011/|title=Professor Margaret Buckingham ForMemRS|date=|work=|publisher=Agence d'evaluation de la recherche et de l'enseignement superieur|doi=|isbn=|accessdate=12 October 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131022213525/https://ged.aeres-evaluation.fr/guest.php?sole=Y&app=AERES_DIFFCV&action=AERES_DIFFCV_DOWNLOAD_CV&id=74011%2F|archivedate=22 October 2013|df=}}</ref>
